{"word":"G4755 - στρατηγός - stratēgós - strat-ay-gos' - Captain","slug":"G4755","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">στρατηγός</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>stratēgós"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>strat-ay-gos'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Captain"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C3;&#x03C4;&#x03C1;&#x03B1;&#x03C4;&#x03B7;&#x03B3;&#x03BF;&#x0301;&#x03C2; - strate&#x0304;gos</b> - <i>strat-ay-gos'</i><p/>From the base of <a href=\"#/G4756\">G4756</a> and <a href=\"#/G71\">G71</a> or <a href=\"#/G2233\">G2233</a>; a <i>general</i>, that is, (by implication or analogy) a (military) <i>governor</i> (<i>praetor</i>), the <i>chief</i> (<i>praefect</i>) of the (Levitical) temple wardens: - captain, magistrate."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G4752\">G4752</a>, <a href=\"#/G4753\">G4753</a>, <a href=\"#/G4754\">G4754</a>, <a href=\"#/G4756\">G4756</a>, <a href=\"#/G4757\">G4757</a>, <a href=\"#/G4758\">G4758</a>, <a href=\"#/G4759\">G4759</a>, <a href=\"#/G4760\">G4760</a>"}]}